In the given code, the POST example uses "resource" as the path, so maybe the GET is for the same resource but with an ID. So maybe the getRequest is for "resource/{id}". Putting it all together, the line should be:

var getRequest = new RestRequest("resource/{id}", Method.GET);

That way, when the parameter "id" is added as a UrlSegment, it replaces the {id} in the path.
